Cut the @onion{2} in half through the root, peel and slice into thin half moon shapes. Peel and finely chop the @garlic cloves{4}(finely chopped). Peel the @carrot{4}, cut them in half lengthways and then chop into half moon shapes about 1cm wide.

Add @oil{2%tbsp} to a #saucepan{} on medium heat and throw in the onions. Cook for ~{6%minutes} before adding in the chopped garlic, carrots, @salt{1/2%tsp} and a good grind of @pepper{}. Cook for a further ~{5%minutes}.

Bring @water{700%ml} to the boil in a #pot{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the rice.

When your carrots have been cooking for ~{5%minutes}, add in the @curry powder mix{1.5%tsp} and @flour{2%tbsp} and cook for ~{1%minute} before adding @water{700%ml} and the @chicken stock pot{1} along with the @honey{2%tbsp} and @soy sauce{3%tbsp}. Stir continuously and bring to a simmer. Leave to cook for ~{10-15%minutes}, then take off the heat, put a #lid{} on, and leave to the side until everything else is ready.

In the meantime, add the @basmati rice{2%cups} to your boiling water, put the lid on and cook for ~{10%minutes} before taking the pot off the heat and leaving for a further ~{10%minutes}.

> Tip: Don't take the lid off the pot until the whole 20 minutes are up!

While your sauce and rice are cooking, prepare your turkey steaks. Put the @British turkey steaks{4} in between two sheets of #clingfilm{} and bash them with a #rolling pin{}, until they are 1cm thick.

Put the @creme fraiche{1} in one #bowl{} and give it a quick stir to loosen it up. Put the @panko breadcrumbs{7%tbsp} in another bowl with @salt{1/2%tsp} and a good grind of @pepper{}. Spread 1 1/2 tsp of crème fraîche onto each side of the turkey steaks. Sprinkle over the panko breadcrumbs and press them into the crème fraîche on the steaks, making sure they are well attached.

When all of your turkey steaks are coated, add @oil{4%tbsp} to a #frying pan{} on medium heat. When the pan is hot, place your turkey steaks in the pan. Cook for ~{5%minutes} on one side (or until golden) before turning over and cooking for ~{4-5%minutes} on the other side.

> Tip: You want your breadcrumbs to be golden brown, so adjust the heat up or down as necessary.

Pop your cooked turkey steaks on some #kitchen paper{} to absorb any excess oil.

> Tip: The turkey is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Serve your rice in bowls with a spoonful of curry sauce on top. Cut your turkey steaks into slices about 2cm wide and pop them on top. Voilà!